Reports declarations of procedures and functions that are missing their implementation in code.
<p>In Oracle, you can declare a procedure or a function without its body, and write the implementation later. The inspection will report names
of such procedures or functions that are left without implementation.</p>
<p>Example (Oracle):</p>
<pre><code>DECLARE PROCEDURE foo(a int, b varchar2);
BEGIN
    NULL;
END;</code></pre>
<p>The <code>foo</code> procedure is declared but is missing implementation. We can add the implementation to get rid of the error.</p>
<pre><code>DECLARE PROCEDURE foo(a int, b varchar2);
  PROCEDURE foo(a int, b varchar2) IS
BEGIN
    NULL;
END;
BEGIN
    NULL;
END;</code></pre>
